# Bugbot review rules (Commercial example)

> Requires Cursor Bugbot on the repository. The template works without Bugbot.

When Bugbot is enabled, customize review focus:

- Security: input validation at API boundaries
- FOSS/commercial compliance per active `.cursor/rules/*-compliance.mdc`
- No secrets in diffs (Gitleaks patterns)
- Prefer Autofix only for lint/type/test nits that map to local `/fix` scope

## Autofix vs FOSS `/fix`

| Path | Use |
|------|-----|
| **Bugbot Autofix** (Cloud Agent credits) | Commercial PR findings that need an isolated fix branch |
| **Local `/fix`** → `watch-gates-autofix` skill | FOSS default after AGENT steps; `scripts/watch-agent-gates.sh --once --autofix` |
| **CI only** | FOSS repos without Bugbot — keep GitHub Actions green |

Do not disable project hooks or Auto-review `block_instructions` for Autofix.

Copy to `.cursor/BUGBOT.md` after `--distribution-tier commercial`.
